title: Magenta Collection (300+ pages) (Eurotica+&hellip;) (2002->)
description:
" A raucous mix of femmes fatales, bondage, and noir, [...] vintage risque and
   kinky, and just as teasing and campy as the best burlesque. [... B]ondage models
   Magenta and Lucretia [... uncover] the seamy underbelly of London of the 60s. " 

  --  from the back cover of "Noir Fatale"

Overview (all in italian, use  <a href=" http://translate.google.com" rel="nofollow" target="_NEW"> http://translate.google.com</a>   as needed):

  <a href=" http://pratocomicsplay.com/index.php/ospiti/ospiti-comics/bio-guerra" rel="nofollow" target="_NEW"> http://pratocomicsplay.com/index.php/ospiti/ospiti-comics/bio-guerra</a>
  <a href=" http://web.cheapnet.it/nikguerra/chronology.html" rel="nofollow" target="_NEW"> http://web.cheapnet.it/nikguerra/chronology.html</a>

Contains:   The two graphic novels

      Invitation to Hell (2002, 2002 Mondo Bizzarro Edition)           (Regdul14)
      Noir Fatale        (2013, 2014 Eurotica Edition)       (Dgtl-HR) (Empire)

   plus a total of 34 scans of 22 distinct shorts, breaking down into

           7 professional English translations from a 2008 SQP volume,
          15 English scanlations from French "Bede Adult" periodicals, circa 2004,
      and 12 HR scans of French translations from 2005/2006 Dynamite volumes.

   The publication history of this title is extremely convoluted, not to mention
   badly documented, including (but not limited to) the unusual circumstance that
   the bulk of the material was published in French and/or English translation
   earlier than in the original Italian, which took place in the "X Comics" erotica
   magazine from 2006. Regardless, the latter dates are the closest thing to an
   official chronology I could uncover, and are thus used for ordering purposes here.
